Djokovic Maintains 2011 Winning Run With Belgrade Title; Davydenko Wins

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-05-01T17:31:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-01/djokovic-maintains-2011-winning-run-with-belgrade-title-davydenko-wins.html
World No. 2 Novak Djokovic maintained
his unbeaten record for the season with a 7-6 (7-4), 6-2 victory
today over Feliciano Lopez of Spain to win tennis’s ATP Serbia
Open in Belgrade.  The 23-year-old Serb has won all five tournaments he’s
entered this year, including the Australian Open and events in
Dubai,  Indian Wells  and Miami. His match record in 2011 is 27-0.  Also today,  Russia ’s Nikolay Davydenko defeated Florian
Mayer of Germany 6-3, 3-6, 6-1 to win an ATP tournament in
Munich.  Juan Martin del Potro of Argentina beat Spain’s Fernando
Verdasco 6-2, 6-2 in the Estoril Open final in Portugal.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty in London at 
